issue_description:
Wrong handling of derived PlannerTerminationConditions
When using PlannerTerminationCondition in the following context:
```cpp
auto c = ompl::base::plannerOrTerminationCondition(
  ob::CostConvergenceTerminationCondition(...),
  ob::IterationTerminationCondition(...)
);
```
the resulting condition `c` is broken: To be passed into [`plannerOrTerminationCondition()`](https://github.com/ompl/ompl/blob/f255ddd60c0ed278b7d7df2b3e37de5e872bac23/src/ompl/base/src/PlannerTerminationCondition.cpp#L197-L204), the _temporary_ sub conditions are auto-converted to `PlannerTerminationConditions` via the defined type-conversion operators, e.g.:
https://github.com/ompl/ompl/blob/f255ddd60c0ed278b7d7df2b3e37de5e872bac23/src/ompl/base/terminationconditions/src/IterationTerminationCondition.cpp#L56-L59

However, the `this` pointer becomes dangling as soon as the temporaries are destroyed, causing [illegal memory access](https://github.com/ros-planning/moveit/pull/2836).

To fix the issue, the type-conversion operator needs to store an instance of the actual condition by capturing a copy:
```cpp
ompl::base::IterationTerminationCondition::operator ompl::base::PlannerTerminationCondition() 
{ 
    auto &c = *this;
    return PlannerTerminationCondition([c] { return c.eval(); }); 
}
``` 

Also, you should explicitly suppress deriving from `PlannerTerminationCondition` but enforce implementing the type-conversion operator instead. Otherwise, a derived condition is passed by reference into a `PlannerTerminationCondition`, which is subsequently copied by value - as the _base_ class, thus missing all members of the derived instance.

