issue_description:
Improve logger interface with a `with_logger` 
@lahwaacz suggested the following improvement, which is very reasonable and should improve our logger interface and usage for solvers.

Btw. it would be nice if there was a `with_logger` member so we could write something like
```cpp
// Create the logger
auto logger = gko::share( gko::log::Convergence< ValueType >::create() );

// Create the solver
auto solver_factory =
      gko::solver::Cg< ValueType >::build()
         .with_criteria(
            gko::stop::Iteration::build()
               .with_max_iters( 1000 )
               .with_logger( logger )
               .on( exec ),
            gko::stop::ResidualNorm< ValueType >::build()
               .with_reduction_factor( 1e-11 )
               .with_logger( logger )
               .on( exec ) )
         .on( exec );
```

instead of
```cpp
// Create the logger
auto logger = gko::share( gko::log::Convergence< ValueType >::create() );

// Create stopping criteria so we can add the logger
auto iter_stop = gko::share(
            gko::stop::Iteration::build()
               .with_max_iters( 1000 )
               .on( exec ) );
auto tol_stop = gko::share(
            gko::stop::ResidualNorm< ValueType >::build()
               .with_reduction_factor( 1e-11 )
               .on( exec ) );
iter_stop->add_logger( logger );
tol_stop->add_logger( logger );

// Create the solver
auto solver_factory =
      gko::solver::Cg< ValueType >::build()
         .with_criteria( iter_stop, tol_stop )
         .on( exec );
```

_Originally posted by @lahwaacz in https://github.com/ginkgo-project/ginkgo/discussions/1099#discussioncomment-3439954_

